Package myAdapter

Class MapAdapter.KeySet

  • java.lang.Object
    • myAdapter.MapAdapter.EntrySet
      • myAdapter.MapAdapter.KeySet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    HCollection, HSet
    Enclosing class:
    MapAdapter
    private class MapAdapter.KeySet
extends MapAdapter.EntrySet

    A HSet which contains all the keys of a MapAdapter, elements of type Object

    Used for the method HMap.keySet(), especially to guarantee the requested backing

    It uses its relative MapAdapter as the unique istance variable

      • equals

        public boolean equals​(java.lang.Object o)
        Compares the specified object with this KeySet for equality. Returns true if and only if the specified object is also a KeySet, both KeySet have the same size, and all corresponding pairs of elements in the two KeySet are equal. (Two elements e1 and e2 are equal if (e1==null ? e2==null : e1.equals(e2)).) In other words, two KeySets are defined to be equal if they contain the same elements in the same order.
        Specified by:

      • hashCode

        public int hashCode()
        Returns the hash code value for this KeySet. The hash code of an KeySet is defined to be the result of the following calculation: hashCode = 1; Iterator i = KeySet.iterator(); while (i.hasNext()) { Object obj = iter.next(); hashCode += obj.hashCode() + (MapAdapter.get(obj)).hashCode(); } This ensures that KeySet1.equals(KeySet2) implies that KeySet1.hashCode()==KeySet2.hashCode() for any two lists, KeySet1 and KeySet2, as required by the general contract of hashCode()
        Specified by:
